<br>
someone said &quot;necro pets have more ac/hp than mage pets&quot;<br>
<br>
heh.. no, depends on the pet, but a mage pet will always beat out a necro pet of equal level. mage pets can be buffed, as well as immune to fear (playing on pvp... if you fear a mages pet, hes just dead...)<br>
<br>
I don't know a hell of alot about mages but ill post what I know.<br>
<br>
Mage nukes do comparable damage to wizzard nukes, yet slower casting time and higher resist. Mages DO get an MR debuff spell.. It has never actually hit on me... so I can't guarantee it will be that effective.<br>
<br>
Mages are very repetitive.. 1 nuke, 4 pets, 1 damage shield every 4 lvls.<br>
<br>
Low level mages are great, wizzards with tanks who can summon supplies...<br>
<br>
mid level I would say mages arent so great, supplies really don't do squat and I would take a wizzard for evac. (of course mages are excellent soloists at this point)<br>
<br>
high level mages are required for raids, Call of Hero is a godsend!<br>
---------------<br>
Necros have weaker pets.. in open field type zones it doesnt really matter, they can simple snare/fear and use their 'mana battery' type spells to regain mana. A necro is a much more mana efficent soloist<br>
<br>
Group wise, other than mana bettery, necros uhh... heal for low low lvls, summon corpse is alright.<br>
<br>
