<br>
Mages will kill something faster than a Necro, but have to med between fights longer.<br>
<br>
Necro fights last longer, but there is less downtime between fights. <br>
<br>
As such, overall downtime is fairly equal, but at least necros get to watch their pet fight while they're medding, while mages get stare at the ground. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I'll give Necros the nod when it comes to safety, however. Not only can they Gate, but if things go bad they have Fear and Feign Death at their disposal. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubalanzsonofanz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balanz son of Anz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 140<br> <font color=#333333>(9/4/01 6:11:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=290.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: MAGE vs. NECRO---Whos the best Solo Artist?</span><hr size=1> I am a mage, and I love being a Mage, but I would have to say <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Necromancers</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> have the edge on us for soloing.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Fear Kiting</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is an awesome thing, and I see necros easily taking on creatures tougher than I can reliably solo.<br>
<br>
But what kicks bootay is partnering with a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> necro</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  Rather than solo side by side <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> (as is often the case at a zone line)</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, partner with them.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Vocarate Water</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> backstabs for 150ish or more, and this works well with <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> kiting</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  Plus <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Maliso</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> reduces all resists except <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> disease</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> by <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 60</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, so that <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Fear</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Darkness</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> stick much better.<br>
<br>
I have wound up pulling for <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Necro</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> partners, and I have been pretty much able to pull continuously.  I pull with <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Maliso</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and make sure it sticks, bring 'em in, and then the necro takes over.  The occasional nuke when the mob threatens to run too far, and we are rocking.<br>
