<br>
If you mean who can solo harder mobs, then the necro easily wins.  <br>
If you mean who can get faster xp soloing, then I would say the magician wins.<br>
<br>
I strongly believe that if a mage and a necro that start at the sametime, play the same hours, and know what they are doing, the mage will get to 50 before the necro will.  In order for necros to efficiently kill, they have to fear and dot.  This means in takes a while for them to kill.  Mages kill much faster, and can kill 2-3 mobs before the necro is done sometimes.  If the mage knows how many hp the stuff hes fighting has, and uses just enough mana to do half damage, then the mage also wont have to med for long before being able to do it again (whoever said mages spend 90% of the time meding, is doing something wrong, or is crazy).  Mages can also get close to almost constant killing by healing fire pets and meding between heals, taking maybe a 30second break every now and then.  The key for a mage is to fight low blues. <p><table border="0">
